# 🛒 MERN Blog App Deployment (FINAL EXAM README)

---

## 🧠 FLOW

```
Create VM → SSH → Setup → Clone → Backend → Frontend → Run → Test → Done
```

---

# 🔑 0. SSH KEY (WSL FIX)

```bash
cp /mnt/c/Users/<your-path>/key.pem ~/
chmod 400 ~/key.pem
```

Connect:

```bash
ssh -i ~/key.pem azureuser@<VM-IP>
```

---

# ⚙️ 1. BASIC SETUP

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y git curl build-essential
```

---

# 💀 2. ADD SWAP (VERY IMPORTANT)

```bash
sudo fallocate -l 1G /swapfile
sudo chmod 600 /swapfile
sudo mkswap /swapfile
sudo swapon /swapfile
```

---

# 🟢 3. INSTALL NODE (v20)

```bash
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs
node -v
```

---

# 🍃 4. INSTALL MONGO (FIXED)

```bash
curl -fsSL https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-6.0.asc | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-6.0.gpg

echo "deb [arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-6.0.gpg] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu jammy/mongodb-org/6.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-6.0.list

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y mongodb-org
sudo systemctl start mongod
```

---

# 📦 5. CLONE PROJECT

```bash
git clone <your-repo>
cd mern-blog-app
```

---

# 🔧 6. BACKEND

```bash
cd backend
npm install
node server.js
```

---

## ✅ TEST BACKEND

Inside VM:

```bash
curl http://localhost:5000/api/blogs
```

From your laptop:

```bash
curl http://<VM-IP>:5000/api/blogs
```

---

## 🧪 TEST POST (VERY IMPORTANT)

```bash
curl -X POST http://<VM-IP>:5000/api/blogs \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"title":"Test Blog","content":"Sample content","author":"JM"}'
```

---

## 🔁 VERIFY DATA

```bash
curl http://<VM-IP>:5000/api/blogs
```

---

👉 Then stop backend:

```bash
CTRL + C
```

---

# 🎨 7. FRONTEND

```bash
cd ../frontend
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install --no-audit --no-fund --legacy-peer-deps
```

Build:

```bash
VITE_API_URL=http://<VM-IP>:5000/api/blogs npm run build
```

---

# 🚀 8. RUN USING PM2

```bash
sudo npm install -g pm2 serve
```

Backend:

```bash
cd ../backend
pm2 start server.js --name "backend"
```

Frontend:

```bash
cd ../frontend
pm2 serve dist 3000 --name "frontend" --spa
```

---

# 🌐 9. ACCESS

```
http://<VM-IP>:3000
```

---

# 🔥 10. AZURE PORTS

Open:

* 3000 (frontend)
* 5000 (backend)

---

# 🐛 DEBUGGING (ALL REAL ISSUES)

---

## SSH KEY ERROR

Fix:

```bash
cp key.pem ~/
chmod 400 key.pem
```

---

## Mongo install fail

Fix:
→ use `jammy` repo

---

## npm error (ENOENT)

Fix:
→ wrong folder → go into backend/frontend

---

## curl fails

Fix:

```bash
node server.js
```

---

## Node version error

Fix:
→ use Node 20

---

## Site not opening

Fix:
→ open port 3000

---

## Vite error

Fix:

```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```

---

## npm hang

Fix:

```bash
npm install --no-audit --no-fund --legacy-peer-deps
```

* ADD SWAP

---

## VM freeze

Fix:
→ restart VM

---

## VM dead

Fix:
→ delete + recreate

---

# 🧠 FINAL RULES

```
node server.js → testing
pm2 start → final
```

```
localhost = current machine
```

```
ALWAYS add swap before npm
```

---

# 😌 FINAL STATUS

If you reach:

```bash
curl http://<VM-IP>:5000/api/blogs
```

👉 and get data

THEN:

```
Backend ✔️
Mongo ✔️
API ✔️
Deployment ✔️
```

